# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0007_3.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (a / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria")))

# ::id dip_test_0007.4 ::date 2022-08-09T08:38:01
# ::snt Absolutely. One of my favorite things about this game is that it can reflect real life history in certain grander strategic considerations, one of which is that, just as would have been the case, neither Germany nor Austria benefits from an antagonistic relationship.
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0007_4.txt
(a / agree-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Austria"))
      :ARG1 (a2 / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a3 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2))
      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany")))

# ::id dip_test_0007.5 ::date 2022-08-09T08:38:34
# ::snt So given the first move, I think the two of us are in a relatively strong position. Turkey seems to be focusing more on Russia than you, and England and France are fighting. Are you going to focus more on Russia or Turkey first? I could try and stop Russia from taking Scandinavia unopposed, but I'd need assurance first that you're going to put pressure on them from the south since a move like Warsaw --> Silesia would screw both of us.
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0007_5.txt
(p / possible-01
      :ARG1 (p2 / prevent-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
            :ARG1 (h / have-03
                  :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                  :ARG1 (w / world-region :name (n3 / name :op1 "Scandinavia")))))

# ::id dip_test_0007.6 ::date 2022-08-09T08:44:33
# ::snt I'm feeling pretty solid about working with Turkey, so Russia is the target for now.
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0007_6.txt
(a / ally-01
      :ARG1 (a2 / and
            :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Austria"))
            :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Turkey"))))

# ::id dip_test_0007.7 ::date 2022-08-09T08:45:11

      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))

            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (a / army

                  :ARG2 (p3 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Tyrolia"))))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria")))

            :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
            :location (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Marseille")))
      :ARG1 (p2 / province))

# ::id dip_test_0011.14 ::date 2022-08-24T11:59:34
# ::snt So, given the moves of England this Fall, it seems clear that they're attacking both of us. I know I've been... aggressive to you in the past, and I know that chances are you won't believe me or agree to work with me, but if you hear me out we both can gain from this (and utterly destroy England in the process). I'll retreat from Burgundy this Spring, and I'll agree to not invade any more territories of yours until all of England is destroyed. I'm assuming you're going to build a fleet in Brest, and if you do so and move Bre --> Eng in the spring it would cut any support that fleet could provide and I can kick England out of the North Sea. From there I can help support you in to the English Channel or we could work to convoy an army into the British Isles in the next few years. I hope you consider.
# ::save-date Tue Oct 4, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0011_14.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (a2 / attack-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 (a3 / and
                  :op1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany"))
                  :op2 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France"))))
      :op2 (e / expect-01
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 (b / build-01
                  :ARG0 c3
                  :ARG1 (f / fleet)
                  :location (p / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Brest"))))
      :op3 (p2 / propose-01
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 (a4 / and
                  :op1 (r / retreat-01
                        :ARG1 (a9 / army
                              :mod c2
                              :location (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Burgundy")))
                        :time (d / date-entity :year 1902
                              :season (s / spring))))
            :ARG3 c3)
      :op4 (a5 / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a6 / and
                  :op1 c2
                  :op2 c3)
            :ARG3 c)
      :op5 (a7 / attack-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 c3)
      :op6 (m / move-01
            :ARG1 (f4 / fleet
                  :mod c3
                  :location p)
            :ARG2 (s2 / sea :name (n6 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel")))
      :op7 (d2 / dislodge-01
            :ARG0 (u4 / unit
                  :mod c2)
            :ARG1 (f2 / fleet
                  :mod c)
            :ARG2 (s3 / sea :name (n7 / name :op1 "North" :op2 "Sea")))
      :op8 (o / or
            :op1 (s4 / support-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (m2 / move-01
                        :ARG1 (f5 / fleet
                              :mod c3)
                        :ARG2 s2))
            :op2 (t / transport-01
                  :ARG0 (f3 / fleet)
                  :ARG1 (a8 / army)
                  :ARG3 (w / world-region :name (n8 / name :op1 "Britain")))))

                  :mod c)

War-Pru, and I’m giving you Tri now, for your build, but basically right after, you should be doing Boh S Tri-Trl, and you’re right smack on where you need to be with all of Trl, Boh, Sil, Pru, and Ber.                         :ARG2 p))
            :ARG3 c)

# ::id dip_test_0017.233 ::date 2022-09-01T09:25:42
# ::snt Our situation with your Vie/Tri centers is tricky: once you recapture Trl, and I'm in Tri, we can press on them, but as long as we need to worry about protecting Vie/Tri from falling into their hands *and* from falling into *my* hands (unintentionally - to keep them out), it'll slow us down, and possibly rob you of the ability to get that last needed northern fleet.
# ::save-date Thu Sep 1, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0017_233.txt

      :ARG1 (b / build-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Russia"))
            :ARG1 (f / fleet)
            :condition (d / defend-01
                  :ARG0 (a / and
                        :op1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Turkey"))
                        :op2 c)
                  :ARG1 (a2 / and
                        :op1 (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Vienna"))
                        :op2 (p3 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Trieste"))))))

# ::id dip_test_0017.234 ::date 2022-09-01T09:30:49
# ::snt For now, I'm doing the Bul-Ser-Bud-Vie choo-choo train, as well as taking Adr and moving Gre-Alb.  If you decide to use Boh S Mun, you probably still want Tri-Trl, but that unit may get wrecked by Ven S Trl-Tri.  I'll take back Tri in the fall, and your army there would have been evaporated in that case, but net effect is it won't change your "available builds" count, and if you stay even elsewhere, you'll still have another F StP to pull out.
# ::save-date Mon Oct 3, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0017_234.txt

      :op1 (m / move-01

            :ARG1 (f / fleet
                  :mod c)
            :ARG2 (s / sea :name (n4 / name :op1 "Adriatic" :op2 "Sea")))
      :op3 (m3 / move-01
            :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                  :mod c
                  :location (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Greece")))
            :ARG2 (p4 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Albania")))
      :op4 (p5 / possible-01
            :ARG1 (s2 / support-01
                  :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n10 / name :op1 "Italy"))
                  :ARG1 (m4 / move-01
                        :ARG1 (a3 / army
                              :location (p7 / province :name (n8 / name :op1 "Tyrolia"))
                              :mod c2)

                        :season (f2 / fall)))))

# ::id dip_test_0017.241 ::date 2022-09-01T11:20:56
# ::snt Your orders look fine.  Since Tri-Trl is moving unsupported and Italy can counterattack, I definitely need to be ready to crush them in Tri in the fall.  We really didn’t help outlet position with this mildly entangled mess in Austria.  As for you keeping Vienna long term: it is all about moving our alliance forward.  Currently you need the builds, so I got you into Vie and then Tri.  You’re fighting three enemies.  But as you focus on just two, and I come into contact with France, I’ll need the builds just as much, so we’ll just keep track of where we need those builds to come from as we press forward!

# ::id dip_test_0017.294 ::date 2022-09-02T12:45:50
# ::snt well, you're building F StP(nc), so you can start sliding Nwy-Ska, Bar S StP-Nwy, and maybe trying to slide Swe-Den somehow.  Then you'll have enough force to make England choose between Nwg and Nth

                              :ARG2 p3))

                        :ARG1 (u3 / unit
                              :mod c

                        :ARG2 (p5 / province :name (n7 / name :op1 "Denmark")))))
      :op4 (p6 / possible-01 :polarity -
            :ARG1 (d / defend-01
                  :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n8 / name :op1 "England"))
                  :ARG1 (a3 / and
                        :op1 (s3 / sea :name (n9 / name :op1 "Norwegian" :op2 "Sea"))

# ::snt F BAL S Nwy - SKA F BAR S Stp/nc - Nwy A Boh S Tyr - Mun A Den S Kie A Kie S Mun - Ruh A Mun - Ruh F Nwy - SKA F Stp/nc - Nwy F Swe S Stp/nc - Nwy A Tyr - Mun A War - Pru

                  :ARG1 (f4 / fleet
                        :mod c

                              :location (n6 / north
                                    :part-of (p2 / province :name (n7 / name :op1 "St." :op2 "Petersburg")))))
                  :ARG2 p)
            :instrument (f3 / fleet
                  :location (s5 / sea :name (n5 / name :op1 "Barents" :op2 "Sea"))))

            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (m3 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (a8 / army
                        :location (p4 / province :name (n9 / name :op1 "Tyrolia"))
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG2 (p5 / province :name (n10 / name :op1 "Munich")))

                  :location (p3 / province :name (n8 / name :op1 "Bohemia"))))
      :op4 (s7 / support-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (p7 / province :name (n12 / name :op1 "Kiel"))
            :instrument (a3 / army
                  :location (p6 / province :name (n11 / name :op1 "Denmark"))))
      :op5 (s8 / support-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (m4 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (a5 / army)
                  :ARG2 (p8 / province :name (n13 / name :op1 "Ruhr")))
            :instrument (a4 / army
                  :location p7
                  :mod c
                  :location p5))
      :op6 (s9 / support-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 m2
            :instrument (f5 / fleet
                  :location (p9 / province :name (n14 / name :op1 "Sweden"))))
      :op7 (m5 / move-01
            :ARG1 (a6 / army))
      :op8 (m6 / move-01
            :ARG1 (a7 / army
                  :mod c
                  :location (p10 / province :name (n15 / name :op1 "Warsaw")))

# ::id dip_test_0017.298 ::date 2022-09-02T12:54:33
# ::snt France just reached out about working together against England
# ::save-date Fri Sep 2, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0017_298.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
      :ARG1 (a / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2)
            :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "England")))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia")))

# ::id dip_test_0017.299 ::date 2022-09-02T12:55:18
# ::snt I think it’s an easy yes from me lol. Put England to bed then we can overrun France in no time. And at this point if I’d rather it end in a 3 way victory than a 5 way
# ::save-date Fri Sep 2, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0017_299.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (a2 / agree-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Russia"))
            :ARG1 (a3 / ally-01
                  :ARG1 (a4 / and
                        :op1 c
                        :op2 c2
                        :op3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France")))
                  :ARG3 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "England")))
            :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Turkey")))
      :op2 (a5 / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a6 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2)
            :ARG3 c3))

# ::id dip_test_0017.300 ::date 2022-09-02T12:58:06
# ::snt Working with France right now will take some pressure of me in the short term and help me put England to bed for good
# ::save-date Fri Sep 2, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0017_300.txt
(a / ally-01
      :ARG1 (a2 / and
            :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Russia"))
            :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Turkey"))
            :op3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France")))
      :ARG3 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "England")))

# ::id dip_test_0017.301 ::date 2022-09-02T12:58:52
# ::snt So IMO, if we want things to move faster, yes, we offer France whatever they want in exchange for them turning on England, and at the same time, be ready to offer England to help them punish the one who stabbed them (France).  So offer Holland to France, totally!
# ::save-date Fri Sep 2, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0017_301.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Turkey"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (p2 / propose-01
                  :ARG0 (a2 / and
                        :op1 c
                        :op2 c2)
                  :ARG1 (a3 / and
                        :op1 (h / have-03
                              :ARG0 c3
                              :ARG1 (p3 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Holland")))
                        :op2 (b / betray-01
                              :ARG0 c3
                              :ARG1 (c4 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "England"))))
                  :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France")))
            :op2 (p4 / propose-01
                  :ARG0 (a4 / and
                        :op1 c
                        :op2 c2)
                  :ARG1 (b2 / betray-01
                        :ARG0 c4
                        :ARG1 c3)
                  :ARG3 c4))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia")))

                              :op1 c2

# ::id dip_test_0017.310 ::date 2022-09-02T13:22:04
# ::snt As for what England is doing with the fleets - they're not telling me, and I know what *I* would do, but I don't know what they would do.

            :condition (h2 / have-03
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Holland")))))

So yeah, I didn’t think you were *planning* to screw me, I just looked at the map and saw: what if England and France just *gave him* the win?       :op2 (p / possible-01
            :ARG1 (a3 / agree-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG2 c)))

# ::id dip_test_0019.29 ::date 2022-09-13T08:05:50
# ::snt Well both of us have only two main competitors left: France and Russia. If we each take on one while the other goes after the other, we’ll kinda split the board up but it’ll be slow.  If we pick the same enemy, it’ll go faster, but we’ll have to leave ourselves a little undefended in the opposite side.  I go after Russia, most likely France grows big in the Med.  You go after France, Russia is breathing down your neck.  That’s my main concern: how do I go after Russia if I know France will quickly be taking control of Italy?  Can we somehow keep France tied down so we’re free to mostly focus on Russia?
# ::save-date Tue Sep 13, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0019_29.txt
(a / amr-empty)

# ::id dip_test_0021.60 ::date 2022-09-14T12:15:15
# ::snt I don't understand people who play this game like it was gunboat.  The game is called diplomacy for a reason: make friends, use those friends to kill everyone off who doesn't have friends, try and convince other people to stop being friends with your enemies, and eventually kill your friends before they kill you.  Forget "the board"... "the dots" - it's about *the people*
# ::save-date Wed Sep 14, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0021_60.txt
(a / amr-empty)

# ::id dip_test_0021.80 ::date 2022-09-15T12:00:04
# ::snt would you have time to be able to stab England if you had a build from Italy, and then we could get Russia to support you into Hol?  With two builds, you could perhaps quickly get to England and kill them fast enough to hold Russia back until I stabbed them in the east, and you worked to control the west?
# ::save-date Thu Sep 15, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0021_80.txt

      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Turkey"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (b / betray-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "England"))
                  :condition (b2 / build-01
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (u / unit)))
            :op2 (s / support-01
                  :ARG0 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                  :ARG1 (m / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                              :mod c2)
                        :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Holland"))))
            :op3 (a2 / attack-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 c3)
            :op4 (d / defend-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG3 c4)
            :op5 (b3 / betray-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 c4))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France")))

                        :ARG1 (u / unit

                        :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Greece"))))
            :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Turkey")))
      :op2 (l / lie-08
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG2 (o / or
                  :op1 c3
                  :op2 c2)))

# ::id dip_test_0026.4 ::date 2022-09-16T06:36:59
# ::snt Looks like Russia is firmly committed South but Germany is gifting them Sweden plus England looks like they wont put up any resistance either. A runaway Russia looks likely. Do you plan to try for Greece?
# ::save-date Fri Sep 16, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0026_4.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (a2 / agree-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))

                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (p / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Sweden")))
            :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia")))
      :op2 (e / expect-01
            :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Italy"))
            :ARG1 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u / unit
                        :mod c3)
                  :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Greece")))
            :polarity (a3 / amr-unknown)))

# ::id dip_test_0026.5 ::date 2022-09-16T06:38:34
# ::snt Only if you'd be willing to support - I'd hold it as the edge of my western expansion, but have no interest in going further. Do you know where Austria plans to go? Turkey-Italy alliance could push Austria north to face Germany and Russia.
# ::save-date Fri Sep 16, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0026_5.txt

            :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy")))
      :ARG2 (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Greece"))
      :condition (s / support-01
            :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Turkey"))
            :ARG1 m))

# ::id dip_test_0026.6 ::date 2022-09-16T06:39:38
# ::snt Yeah fair enough. I can't be sure of what Austria plans to do now as they seem to be spreading misinformation pretty liberally according to Russia.                   :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Austria")))
            :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Turkey")))
      :op2 (p / possible-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / agree-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (s / support-01
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (m / move-01
                              :ARG1 (u / unit
                                    :mod c4)
                              :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Greece"))))
                  :ARG2 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Italy"))))
      :op3 (p3 / possible-01
            :ARG1 (a3 / ally-01
                  :ARG1 (a4 / and
                        :op1 c2
                        :op2 c4)))
      :op4 (t2 / trust-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG2 (a5 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c3)))

# ::id dip_test_0026.12 ::date 2022-09-16T06:48:17
# ::snt I cant support you into Greece, but I can support you into TRI in the fall
# ::save-date Fri Sep 16, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0026_12.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (r / reject-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Turkey"))
            :ARG1 (p / propose-01
                  :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy"))
                  :ARG1 (s / support-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (m / move-01
                              :ARG1 (u / unit
                                    :mod c2)
                              :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Greece"))))
                  :ARG3 c))
      :op2 (p3 / propose-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (s2 / support-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (m2 / move-01
                              :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                                    :mod c2)
                              :ARG2 (p4 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Trieste")))
                        :time (d / date-entity
                              :season (f / fall)))
                  :op2 (r2 / retreat-01
                        :ARG1 (u3 / unit
                              :mod c2)
                        :destination (p5 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Naples")))
                  :op3 (r3 / retreat-01 :polarity -
                        :ARG1 u3
                        :destination (p6 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Albania"))))
            :ARG3 c2))

                  :ARG0 (f2 / fleet

                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 d
                  :instrument (f3 / fleet))
            :ARG3 c4))

            :op1 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (f / fleet

            :op2 (s2 / support-01
                  :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n6 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                  :ARG1 (u / unit
                        :mod c3
                        :location p2))))

# ::id dip_test_0038.1 ::date 2022-10-18T13:57:22
# ::snt Greetings from the South! Hope you are doing well! Wondering if we might be able to build a good relationship. Do you prefer to bounce in the black sea?
# ::save-date Tue Oct 18, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0038_1.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Turkey"))
      :ARG1 (b / bounce-03
            :ARG1 (a / and
                  :op1 (f / fleet
                        :mod c)
                  :op2 (f2 / fleet
                        :mod c2))
            :ARG3 (s / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "Black" :op2 "Sea")))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia")))

# ::id dip_test_0038.2 ::date 2022-10-18T13:58:53

                  :mod c2)
            :ARG2 (a5 / and
                  :op1 (p / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Galicia"))
                  :op2 (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Ukraine")))

                        :op1 (u2 / unit

                        :op2 (u3 / unit

                  :ARG3 (s / sea :name (n5 / name :op1 "Black" :op2 "Sea")))

# ::id dip_test_0038.18 ::date 2022-10-18T14:31:10
# ::snt OK I understand your hesitancy over BLA. Yes, Austria is spreading a lot of misinformation, to Italy as well as us. There are three things here and I can only give up one otherwise I'm putting myself under way too much risk. Its either 1) you taking RUM by yourself and I wont try and stop it 2) black sea DMZ (but we'd need to bounce it) 3) me supporting you into Rum. Whichever one you take, I can't give up any of the others. # ::save-date Tue Oct 18, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0038_18.txt

      :op1 (l / lie-08
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Austria"))
            :ARG2 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy"))
                  :op2 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Turkey"))
                  :op3 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Russia"))))
      :op2 (p / propose-01
            :ARG0 c3
            :ARG1 (o / or
                  :op1 (a3 / attack-01
                        :ARG0 c4
                        :ARG1 (p2 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Romania")))
                  :op2 (a4 / and
                        :op1 (d / demilitarize-01
                              :ARG1 (a5 / and
                                    :op1 c3
                                    :op2 c4))
                        :op2 (b / bounce-03
                              :ARG1 (a6 / and
                                    :op1 (u / unit
                                          :mod c3)
                                    :op2 (u2 / unit
                                          :mod c4))
                              :ARG3 (s / sea :name (n6 / name :op1 "Black" :op2 "Sea")))))
            :ARG3 c4)

            :ARG0 c3
            :ARG1 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u3 / unit
                        :mod c4)
                  :ARG2 p2))
      :op4 (a7 / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a8 / and
                  :op1 c4
                  :op2 c3)))

# ::id dip_test_0038.19 ::date 2022-10-18T14:35:03

                        :ARG0 c

                  :op1 c3

# ::id dip_test_0041.131 ::date 2022-10-21T12:11:23
# ::snt While I reasonably hesitated to involve myself in the conflict with a Germany, the fact that I have taken Denmark (and intend to continue attacking with the fleet in Denmark) ought to indicate that I'm no longer hesitating to commit. While Turkey/Austria is a significant threat in the late game, I'm also concerned with not being eliminated in the short-term. The fact of the matter is that I am surrounded by powers who can stab me with devastating effect (you) or powers who have in fact stabbed me (Russia) or would stab if given the chance (Germany). I am more than willing to hit Germany right now and move South from Denmark, but I also need to cover my bases and get Nor. Russia can have centers in Germany to combat AT.
# ::save-date Fri Oct 21, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_test_0041_131.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (f / fear-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 (b / betray-01
                  :ARG0 (o / or
                        :op1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France"))
                        :op2 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                        :op3 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Germany")))
                  :ARG1 c))
      :op2 (a2 / agree-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (a3 / and
                  :op1 (a4 / attack-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 c4
                        :time (d / date-entity :year 1903
                              :season (s / spring)))
                  :op2 (m / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u / unit
                              :mod c
                              :location (p / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Denmark")))
                        :direction (s2 / south)))
            :ARG2 c2))

                              :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Silesia")))))
            :op2 (p3 / propose-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (a3 / and
                        :op1 (s2 / support-01
                              :ARG0 c2
                              :ARG1 (h / hold-03
                                    :ARG0 c2
                                    :ARG1 p2)
                              :instrument (a4 / army
                                    :location (p4 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Warsaw"))))
                        :op2 (s3 / support-01
                              :ARG0 (c4 / country :name (n7 / name :op1 "England"))
                              :ARG1 (m2 / move-01
                                    :ARG1 (a5 / army
                                          :location (p6 / province :name (n9 / name :op1 "Munich")))
                                    :ARG2 (p7 / province :name (n10 / name :op1 "Berlin")))
                              :instrument (u / unit
                                    :location (p5 / province :name (n8 / name :op1 "Kiel"))))
                        :op3 (m3 / move-01
                              :ARG1 (a6 / army
                                    :location (p8 / province :name (n11 / name :op1 "Burgundy")))
                              :ARG2 p6))
                  :ARG3 c2))

# ::id dip_train_0004.29 ::date 2022-06-07T10:51:52
# ::snt France has FOUR armies, and now he has a wide open runway to roll right over Germany. If you help him, you’re going to regret it. Look two game years ahead, France is going to be in a crazy good position.   On the other hand, if you change course now and go get France instead, France is NEVER going to be able to build a second fleet. He will be so much easier to destroy. And Germany is so green...he’ll be much easier to take down second.   I just...I can see where this is headed. I know it’s attractive just to take that easy build. But that is the apple of knowledge and France is the devilish serpent (end part 2)
# ::save-date Fri Jun 17, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0004_29.txt

      :ARG1 (b / build-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
            :ARG1 (f / fleet))
      :condition (a / attack-01
            :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 c))

# ::id dip_train_0004.30 ::date 2022-06-07T10:53:11

# ::save-date Tue Jun 7, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0004_30.txt

                  :op1 c

            :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France")))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England")))

# ::id dip_train_0004.58 ::date 2022-06-07T12:18:18
# ::snt I can move to attack France in the Spring if you like. For now, I think that mobilizing Germany to attack France is your best bet (and shouldn’t be too hard).
# ::save-date Tue Jun 7, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0004_58.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (a2 / attack-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France"))
                  :time (d / date-entity :year 1904
                        :season (s / spring)))
            :op2 (p2 / propose-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (a3 / attack-01
                        :ARG0 c4
                        :ARG1 c3)
                  :ARG3 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Germany"))))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England")))

# ::id dip_train_0004.59 ::date 2022-06-07T12:21:04
# ::snt You know what? This isn’t really fair of me. If you will commit to the France attack, I’ll move on him now. Are you ready to go all out against him? This could actually work out really well for both of us.
# ::save-date Tue Jun 7, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0004_59.txt
(a / attack-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France"))
      :condition (a2 / attack-01
            :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 c2)
      :time (d / date-entity :year 1903
            :season (s / spring)))

# ::id dip_train_0004.60 ::date 2022-06-07T12:23:44
# ::snt I’m ready, but i may want your advice on some of the tactics. My plan is to completely cold shoulder France in negotiations and start an attack. We’ll want to get germany on board, but I think Germany is playing a bit neutral for survival purposes right now.
# ::save-date Tue Jun 7, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0004_60.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (a2 / attack-01
            :ARG0 (a3 / and
                  :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
                  :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy")))
            :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France")))
      :op2 (p / propose-01
            :ARG0 (a4 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2)
            :ARG1 (a5 / attack-01
                  :ARG0 c4
                  :ARG1 c3)
            :ARG3 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Germany"))))

# ::id dip_train_0004.61 ::date 2022-06-07T12:27:20
# ::snt I agree with regard to Germany’s strategy, but I believe he hates France most and he will be with you if both you and I move on France now.   France is getting no builds. Let’s just put the clamps on now! I will move to TYS and Tun if you will move either to take Belgium, or to position your fleets at Irish/Channel.   If we both take the plunge, there is nothing he can do.
# ::save-date Wed Sep 28, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0004_61.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (e / expect-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
            :ARG1 (a2 / attack-01
                  :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany"))
                  :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France"))
                  :condition (a3 / attack-01
                        :ARG0 (a4 / and
                              :op1 c
                              :op2 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "England")))
                        :ARG1 c3
                        :time (d / date-entity :year 1903
                              :season (f / fall)))))
      :op2 (b / build-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 c3
            :ARG1 (u / unit))
      :op3 (p / propose-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (a5 / and
                  :op1 (m / move-01
                        :ARG1 (f3 / fleet
                              :mod c)
                        :ARG2 (a6 / and
                              :op1 (s / sea :name (n5 / name :op1 "Tyrrhenian" :op2 "Sea"))
                              :op2 (p2 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Tunisia"))))
                  :op2 (m2 / move-01
                        :ARG1 (f2 / fleet
                              :mod c4)
                        :ARG2 (o / or
                              :op1 (p3 / province :name (n7 / name :op1 "Belgium"))
                              :op2 (s2 / sea :name (n8 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel"))
                              :op3 (s3 / sea :name (n9 / name :op1 "Irish" :op2 "Sea")))))
            :ARG3 c4))

# ::id dip_train_0004.62 ::date 2022-06-07T12:32:47
# ::snt France can support himself into England though, and I think he plans to because he was asking for Germany to cut support in Nth (which she plans not to). The only way to hold the channel is to support from Nth.
# ::save-date Wed Sep 28, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0004_62.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (p / possible-01
            :ARG1 (h / hold-03
                  :ARG1 (s / sea :name (n / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel")))
            :condition (s2 / support-01
                  :instrument (f / fleet
                        :location (s3 / sea :name (n2 / name :op1 "North" :op2 "Sea")))))
      :op2 (e / expect-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (s4 / support-01
                        :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "France"))
                        :ARG1 (m / move-01
                              :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                                    :mod c2)
                              :ARG2 s))
                  :op2 (p2 / prevent-01 :polarity -
                        :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Germany"))
                        :ARG1 (s5 / support-01
                              :instrument (f2 / fleet
                                    :location s3))))))

# ::id dip_train_0004.64 ::date 2022-06-07T12:39:24
# ::snt I'm planning army yorkshire to wales, which allows for the convoy through the channel next year, and allows me to bounce in Lvp if France moves to IRI

            :ARG1 (a2 / army
                  :location (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Yorkshire"))
                  :mod (c3 / country :name (n / name :op1 "England")))
            :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Wales")))
      :op2 (p3 / possible-01
            :ARG1 (a3 / and
                  :op1 (t / transport-01
                        :ARG0 (f2 / fleet)
                        :ARG1 (u2 / unit)
                        :ARG4 (s / sea :name (n4 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel"))
                        :time (d / date-entity :year 1904))
                  :op2 (b / bounce-03
                        :ARG1 (u3 / unit
                              :mod c3)
                        :ARG3 (p4 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Liverpool"))
                        :condition (m2 / move-01
                              :ARG1 (f / fleet
                                    :mod (c / country :name (n6 / name :op1 "France")))

# ::id dip_train_0004.77 ::date 2022-06-08T06:49:49

                        :ARG0 c2

                                    :ARG1 u
                                    :ARG2 p4)
                              :instrument (u3 / unit
                                    :mod c3
                                    :location (p6 / province :name (n8 / name :op1 "Bohemia"))))
                        :ARG3 c3)

                        :ARG0 c2

                              :op1 (b / build-01 :polarity -
                                    :ARG0 c4
                                    :ARG1 (u4 / unit))
                              :op2 (a5 / ally-01 :polarity -
                                    :ARG1 (a6 / and
                                          :op1 c
                                          :op2 c4)))
                        :condition s))
            :ARG2 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Russia")))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England")))

# ::id dip_train_0004.258 ::date 2022-06-09T11:33:24
# ::snt Hmmm, interesting French disband. He wants me to support him to Brest. Have to believe he’s going to have Germany on his side given the German fleet build.   Thoughts on how to approach this? We should be able to defeat them if we stick together.
# ::save-date Fri Jun 17, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0004_258.txt

      :op1 (p / propose-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
            :ARG1 (s / support-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (m / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u / unit
                              :mod c)
                        :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Brest"))))
            :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy")))
      :op2 (b / build-01
            :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Germany"))
            :ARG1 (f / fleet))
      :op3 (p3 / propose-01
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 (a2 / ally-01
                  :ARG1 (a3 / and
                        :op1 c2
                        :op2 c4)
                  :ARG3 (a4 / and
                        :op1 c

            :ARG0 c3

                        :ARG1 (a4 / army
                              :mod c2)
                        :ARG2 c2))

                  :ARG0 c3
                  :ARG1 (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Brest"))))
      :op3 (p3 / propose-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (s2 / support-01
                  :ARG0 c3
                  :ARG1 (m2 / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u / unit
                              :mod (c4 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "France")))
                        :ARG2 p2))

                        :mod c2)

                  :purpose (d / defend-01 :polarity -
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (p5 / province)))
            :ARG3 c2))

      :op1 (p / possible-01
            :ARG1 (b / bounce-03
                  :ARG1 (u / unit
                        :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England")))

            :ARG3 c2))

                        :ARG0 c

# ::snt Yeah, I think on balance I have to give him the option to follow through, and have a reason to deescalate with me so he can join the dogpile on France.  Odds are high I'm going to regret the decision and end up offering you that support in the Fall when you can't reciprocate, but I gotta take the chance with Austria obviously spoiling for a fight.

            :op1 (a2 / agree-01

                        :ARG0 c

                              :season (f / fall)))
                  :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany")))
            :op2 (a3 / attack-01
                  :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Austria"))
                  :ARG1 c)))

      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England")))

(h / have-03
      :ARG0 (o / or
            :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
            :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia")))
      :ARG1 (p / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Kiel"))

            :season (s / spring)))

      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Russia"))

# ::id dip_train_0008.26 ::date 2022-06-15T07:55:17
# ::snt Are you and England planning to high-five in Sweden and Norway again this turn?  I still think supporting Rumania into Gal from Sil is a good move for you. It's getting to the point where (if I'm able to rebuild a unit this winter) I think it'd be worth teaming up to knock Austria down a peg
# ::save-date Mon Jun 20, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0008_26.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (s / support-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (m / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                              :mod c2
                              :location (p3 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Romania")))
                        :ARG2 (p4 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Galicia")))
                  :instrument (u / unit
                        :mod c2
                        :location (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Silesia"))))
            :op2 (a2 / ally-01
                  :ARG1 (a3 / and
                        :op1 c
                        :op2 c2)
                  :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n6 / name :op1 "Austria"))
                  :condition (b / build-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (u3 / unit)
                        :time (d / date-entity :year 1904
                              :season (f / fall)))))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia")))

# ::id dip_train_0008.27 ::date 2022-06-15T07:59:59

# ::id dip_train_0008.28 ::date 2022-06-15T08:00:10

# ::save-date Wed Jun 15, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0008_28.txt

# ::id dip_train_0008.30 ::date 2022-06-15T08:05:44
# ::snt England has been talking with me about a Russia-Germany-England alliance, and I agree with them that it's the only thing that makes sense in the face of the Austria-Italy powerhouse. I assume England's been speaking with you as well, and just wanted to confirm the three of us are on the same page.   On that note, the moves I have planned for this year are all geared towards attacking the west, but I am happy to change my plans if you want some support or coordination to the east.
# ::save-date Wed Jun 15, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0008_30.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (p / propose-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 (a2 / ally-01
                  :ARG1 (a3 / and
                        :op1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                        :op2 c2
                        :op3 c)
                  :ARG3 (a4 / and
                        :op1 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Austria"))
                        :op2 (c5 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Italy"))))
            :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany")))
      :op2 (a5 / agree-01
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG2 c)
      :op3 (a6 / agree-01
            :ARG0 c3
            :ARG2 (a8 / and
                  :op1 c2
                  :op2 c)
            :polarity (a7 / amr-unknown)))

# ::id dip_train_0008.31 ::date 2022-06-15T08:32:12

      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Russia"))

            :ARG1 (a2 / attack-01
                  :ARG1 (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Munich"))
                  :time (d / date-entity :year 1906
                        :season (f / fall)))
            :polarity (a3 / amr-unknown)))

# ::id dip_train_0009.39 ::date 2022-06-15T12:04:56
# ::snt So my reasoning is that I think France is a stronger player than either of us, or at least a more engaged one. I'm getting all this tactical analysis and commentary about the state of the whole board and all that. If I help France, France probably beats me. If we defeat France together, I think we each end up with an even fighting chance.
# ::save-date Thu Jun 16, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0009_39.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
      :ARG1 (a / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2)
            :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France")))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany")))

# ::id dip_train_0009.42 ::date 2022-06-16T06:37:53
# ::snt Haha yeah that was kind of my thinking. Russia is a little tied up in the south, and so I don't expect aggression in the north. However, france would respond to a stab by begging for Russian (and potentially austrian and italian) assistance. So the choice next year is between containing russia or being aggressive (which would mean going for sweden or St. P). I think the builds we see this winter will make it more clear what's possible.
# ::save-date Thu Jun 16, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0009_42.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (e / expect-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (a3 / attack-01 :polarity -
                        :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia")))))
      :op2 (a4 / ally-01
            :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France"))
            :ARG2 (o / or
                  :op1 c2
                  :op2 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Austria"))
                  :op3 (c5 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Italy")))
            :condition (b / betray-01
                  :ARG1 c3))
      :op3 (p / possible-01
            :ARG1 (o2 / or
                  :op1 (p2 / prevent-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (a5 / attack-01
                              :ARG0 c2))
                  :op2 (a6 / attack-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (o3 / or
                              :op1 (p3 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Sweden"))
                              :op2 (p4 / province :name (n7 / name :op1 "St." :op2 "Petersburg")))))
            :time (d / date-entity :year 1902)))

# ::id dip_train_0009.43 ::date 2022-06-16T06:46:19
# ::snt Speaking of, what are your planned builds? I'm building a fleet in London.

      :ARG1 (f / fleet)
      :location (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "London")))

      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (a2 / army
                  :mod c
                  :location (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Kiel")))
            :op2 (a3 / army
                  :mod c
                  :location (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Munich")))))

# ::id dip_train_0009.45 ::date 2022-06-16T06:47:40
# ::snt What are your plans for your north sea and London fleets?  I'm trying to decide now how best to handle Belgium and that is going to depend on whether France is concerned with defending Brest or if instead they expect help from you in disrupting anything I try to do from Holland.   ...I can offer you support in moving into Sweden in exchange for supporting my Burgundy troops into Belgium? Is that worth more than whatever France might be offering you right now?
# ::save-date Mon Jun 20, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0009_45.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (p / possible-01
            :ARG1 (o / or
                  :op1 (d / defend-01
                        :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
                        :ARG1 (p2 / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Brest")))
                  :op2 (p3 / prevent-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (m / move-01
                              :ARG1 (u / unit
                                    :mod (c2 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Germany"))
                                    :location (p4 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Holland")))))))
      :op2 (p5 / propose-01
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (s / support-01
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (m2 / move-01
                              :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                                    :mod c3)
                              :ARG2 (p6 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Sweden"))))
                  :op2 (s2 / support-01
                        :ARG0 c3
                        :ARG1 (m3 / move-01
                              :ARG1 (a3 / army
                                    :mod c2
                                    :location (p7 / province :name (n7 / name :op1 "Burgundy")))
                              :ARG2 (p8 / province :name (n8 / name :op1 "Belgium")))))
            :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "England"))))

# ::id dip_train_0009.50 ::date 2022-06-16T06:49:14
# ::snt My once concern about the full-on france stab would be that the job couldn't be done quickly enough. (e / expect-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (p / possible-01 :polarity -
                  :ARG1 (b / betray-01
                        :ARG0 (a2 / and
                              :op1 c
                              :op2 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Germany")))
                        :ARG1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France"))
                        :time (d / date-entity :year 1902)))
            :op2 (p2 / possible-01
                  :ARG1 (h / have-03
                        :ARG0 (a3 / and
                              :op1 c
                              :op2 c3)
                        :ARG1 (p3 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Belgium"))
                        :time (d2 / date-entity :year 1902)))
            :op3 (h2 / have-03
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (p4 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Spain")))
            :op4 (p5 / possible-01
                  :ARG1 (b2 / build-01
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (u / unit)
                        :location (p6 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Brest"))
                        :condition (d3 / dislodge-01
                              :ARG1 (a4 / army)
                              :ARG2 p3)))))

                              :mod c

# ::id dip_train_0009.58 ::date 2022-06-16T07:34:53
# ::snt Keep your fleets in NWG and NTH, but move to ENG. Have NTH support HOL-BEL.  I'll attack BUR-PIC, move KIE-RUH, MUN-BUR. You still get my support to march on Sweden in Fall if desired.
# ::save-date Tue Oct 4, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0009_58.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (p / propose-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (h / hold-03
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (a3 / and
                              :op1 (s / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "Norwegian" :op2 "Sea"))
                              :op2 (s2 / sea :name (n4 / name :op1 "North" :op2 "Sea"))))
                  :op2 (m / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u / unit
                              :mod c2)
                        :ARG2 (s4 / sea :name (n17 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel")))
                  :op3 (s3 / support-01
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (m2 / move-01
                              :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                                    :location (p2 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Holland")))
                              :ARG2 (p3 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Belgium")))
                        :instrument (f / fleet
                              :mod c2
                              :location s2))
                  :op4 (a4 / attack-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (p4 / province :name (n7 / name :op1 "Picardy"))
                        :instrument (u3 / unit
                              :mod c
                              :location (p5 / province :name (n8 / name :op1 "Burgundy"))))
                  :op5 (m3 / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u4 / unit
                              :location (p6 / province :name (n9 / name :op1 "Kiel"))
                              :mod c)
                        :ARG2 (p7 / province :name (n10 / name :op1 "Ruhr")))
                  :op6 (m4 / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u5 / unit
                              :mod c
                              :location (p8 / province :name (n11 / name :op1 "Munich")))
                        :ARG2 p5))
            :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England")))
      :op2 (e / expect-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (a5 / and
                  :op1 (l / lose-02
                        :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n12 / name :op1 "France"))
                        :ARG1 (a6 / and
                              :op1 (p9 / province :name (n13 / name :op1 "Brest"))
                              :op2 (p10 / province :name (n14 / name :op1 "Paris"))
                              :op3 (p11 / province :name (n15 / name :op1 "Marseille")))
                        :condition (p12 / prevent-01
                              :ARG0 c3
                              :ARG1 (m5 / move-01
                                    :ARG1 (u6 / unit)
                                    :ARG2 (p13 / province :name (n16 / name :op1 "Gascony")))))
                  :op2 (r / retreat-01
                        :ARG1 (u8 / unit
                              :mod c)
                        :destination p13
                        :condition (d / dislodge-01
                              :ARG1 (u7 / unit
                                    :mod c))))))

# ::id dip_train_0009.613 ::date 2022-06-27T12:25:07

# ::id dip_train_0009.657 ::date 2022-06-27T13:39:37
# ::snt Ok would you be up for: Paris support Brest Hold, and then get one of your fleets into the channel? And then don't go to Nth as I'll be moving Nth to NWG and Denmark to Nth to make sure he can't break through in the north? Yor holds?
# ::save-date Tue Jun 28, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0009_657.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (s / support-01
                  :ARG1 (h / hold-03
                        :ARG1 (p3 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Brest")))
                  :instrument (u / unit
                        :location (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Paris"))))
            :op2 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (f / fleet
                        :mod c2)
                  :ARG2 (s2 / sea :name (n5 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel")))
            :op3 (m2 / move-01 :polarity -
                  :ARG1 (f2 / fleet
                        :mod c2)
                  :ARG2 (s3 / sea :name (n6 / name :op1 "North" :op2 "Sea")))
            :op4 (m3 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (f3 / fleet
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG2 (s4 / sea :name (n7 / name :op1 "Norwegian" :op2 "Sea")))
            :op5 (m4 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                        :mod c
                        :location (p4 / province :name (n8 / name :op1 "Denmark")))
                  :ARG2 s3)
            :op6 (h2 / hold-03
                  :ARG1 (p5 / province :name (n9 / name :op1 "Yorkshire"))))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany")))

# ::id dip_train_0009.658 ::date 2022-06-27T13:42:18
# ::snt Pic support Brest hold as well would guarantee that he can't take it from the channel.
# ::save-date Wed Sep 28, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0009_658.txt

      :ARG1 (h / have-03
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
            :ARG1 (p2 / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Brest"))
            :instrument (f / fleet
                  :mod c
                  :location (s / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel"))))
      :condition (s2 / support-01
            :ARG1 (h2 / hold-03
                  :ARG1 p2)
            :instrument (u2 / unit
                  :location (p3 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Picardy")))))

                        :location (p3 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Picardy"))))
            :ARG3 c2))

# ::id dip_train_0009.666 ::date 2022-06-27T13:48:27
# ::snt Wait I'm actually doing our moves wrong if we want to hold paris. I need to attack Gas from Bre. Otherwise, Eng cuts Bre support, Gas supports Bur to Par. So I'm going to do that instead.

            :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "England"))

                  :op1 (p / prevent-01
                        :ARG1 (s / support-01
                              :ARG1 (p2 / province :name (n / name :op1 "Brest")))

                              :location p4))
                  :op2 (s2 / support-01
                        :ARG1 (m / move-01
                              :ARG1 (u3 / unit
                                    :location (p3 / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Burgundy")))
                              :ARG2 p2)
                        :instrument (u2 / unit
                              :location p4))))
      :op2 (a3 / attack-01
            :ARG0 c3
            :ARG1 (p4 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Gascony"))
            :instrument (u4 / unit
                  :location p2)
            :purpose (h / hold-03
                  :ARG0 (a4 / and
                        :op1 c3
                        :op2 (c2 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Germany")))
                  :ARG1 p2)))

            :ARG0 c

                  :op1 (p4 / prevent-01
                        :ARG1 (s / support-01

                                    :ARG1 (o / or
                                          :op1 (p5 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Brest"))
                                          :op2 p2))))
                  :op2 (b / bounce-03
                        :ARG1 (a4 / army)))
            :condition m))

                                    :location (p5 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Paris"))))

# ::id dip_train_0012.2 ::date 2022-06-30T05:59:54
# ::snt Hey hey!   Don't really have much of a plan yet - like you, I generally try not to piss off too many people at the start until I get a feel for the lay of the board, so my general decision at start is really just Mos -> Ukr|StP .  Right now my default inclination is to go Ukr and try to get Rum, that may change as I talk to other players.  Happy to talk about trying to take that with fleet or army depending on how spring goes, and certainly not looking to commit to any particular long-term growth direction right now.  That being said, A/R is one of my favorite duos (R/F is up there too, but I don't think I've ever even seriously tried to pull that off in an online game - that's a FtF option where I know the players 😃 ).       :op1 (e / expect-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Russia"))
            :ARG1 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u / unit

                  :ARG2 (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Ukraine"))))
      :op2 (p2 / possible-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (h / have-03
                        :ARG0 c

                              :op1 c

            :ARG1 (u / unit
                  :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))))
      :op2 (e / expect-01
            :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France"))
            :ARG1 (a2 / attack-01 :polarity -
                  :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                  :ARG1 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Germany"))))
      :op3 (p / possible-01
            :ARG1 (a3 / attack-01 :polarity -
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 c4)
            :condition (s / support-01
                  :ARG0 (c5 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Italy"))
                  :ARG1 a2)))

# ::id dip_train_0018.26 ::date 2022-07-01T09:42:43

      :op1 (p / propose-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
            :ARG1 (b / build-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (f / fleet))
            :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany")))
      :op2 (p2 / possible-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / attack-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "England"))))
      :op3 (p3 / possible-01
            :ARG1 (a3 / ally-01 :polarity -
                  :ARG1 (a4 / and
                        :op1 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Austria"))
                        :op2 (c5 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Italy"))))))

                  :ARG1 (m / move-01

                        :ARG2 (s / south))

      :op2 (a2 / agree-01
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 (s2 / sea :name (n4 / name :op1 "Black" :op2 "Sea"))

            :polarity (a3 / amr-unknown)))

# ::snt I'd like to leave it unoccupied. A fight early on is bad for both of us.
# ::save-date Fri Jul 8, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0020_3.txt

      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
      :ARG1 (d / demilitarize-01
            :ARG1 (a / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2)
            :ARG2 (s / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel")))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France")))

# ::id dip_train_0020.5 ::date 2022-07-08T09:45:20

      :op1 (p / propose-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 (d / demilitarize-01
                  :ARG1 (a2 / and
                        :op1 c
                        :op2 c2)
                  :ARG2 (s / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel"))
                  :time (d2 / date-interval :op1 1901 :op2 1902))
            :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France")))
      :op2 (m / move-01
            :ARG1 (f / fleet
                  :mod c2)
            :ARG2 (s2 / sea :name (n4 / name :op1 "Mid-Atlantic" :op2 "Ocean"))
            :polarity (a3 / amr-unknown))
      :op3 (t / tell-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (m2 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (a4 / army
                        :mod c)
                  :direction (n5 / north))
            :ARG2 c2)
      :op4 (p2 / possible-01
            :ARG1 (m3 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u / unit
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG2 (p3 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Belgium")))))

      :op1 (p / possible-01
            :ARG1 (s / support-01
                  :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
                  :ARG1 (m / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u / unit
                              :mod (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England")))
                        :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Belgium")))))
      :op2 (b / build-01
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 (a2 / army)
            :location (p3 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "London")))
      :op3 (b2 / build-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 (f / fleet)
            :location p3)
      :op4 (a3 / attack-01
            :ARG0 (a4 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2)
            :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Germany"))
            :time (d / date-entity :year 1901
                  :season (f2 / fall)))
      :op5 (p4 / prevent-01
            :ARG0 (a5 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2)
            :ARG1 (m2 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u2 / unit)
                  :ARG2 (p5 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Holland")))))

                              :op1 c

# ::id dip_train_0020.128 ::date 2022-07-13T11:33:52
# ::snt What's the plan on the German front? Maybe we can get creative with the moves in a way that gets both of us at least one dot. I'm not holding myy breath on Ruhr, so I think the best play might be to send Belgium to Holland with support from the north sea while Denmark hits Kiel with support from Helgoland. If Germany makes similar moves to her last turn, we would pop both Kiel and Holland and would guarantee Munich/Berlin for next year. If Germany supports Kiel instead of moving to Ruhr, then we would guarantee Kiel in the fall as I'd walk into Ruhr and we would have Ruhr, Holland, Helgoland, and Denmark for a 4V3.
# ::save-date Thu Sep 29, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0020_128.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (p / propose-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (s / support-01
                        :ARG0 (f2 / fleet
                              :location (s2 / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "North" :op2 "Sea")))
                        :ARG1 (m / move-01
                              :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                                    :location (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Belgium")))
                              :ARG2 (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Holland"))))
                  :op2 (s3 / support-01
                        :ARG0 (f3 / fleet
                              :location (s4 / sea :name (n6 / name :op1 "Heligoland" :op2 "Bight")))
                        :ARG1 (a3 / attack-01
                              :ARG0 (u4 / unit
                                    :location (p4 / province :name (n7 / name :op1 "Denmark")))
                              :ARG1 (p5 / province :name (n8 / name :op1 "Kiel")))))
            :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England")))
      :op2 (e / expect-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (a4 / and
                  :op1 (h / have-03
                        :ARG0 (a5 / and
                              :op1 c
                              :op2 c2)
                        :ARG1 (a6 / and
                              :op1 p5
                              :op2 p3))
                  :op2 (h2 / have-03
                        :ARG0 (a7 / and
                              :op1 c
                              :op2 c2)
                        :ARG1 (a8 / and
                              :op1 (p6 / province :name (n9 / name :op1 "Munich"))
                              :op2 (p7 / province :name (n10 / name :op1 "Berlin")))
                        :time (d / date-entity :year 1904))
                  :op3 (h3 / have-03
                        :ARG0 (a9 / and
                              :op1 c
                              :op2 c2)
                        :ARG1 p5
                        :time (d2 / date-entity
                              :season (f / fall))
                        :condition (a10 / and
                              :op1 (s5 / support-01
                                    :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n11 / name :op1 "Germany"))
                                    :ARG1 p5)
                              :op2 (m2 / move-01 :polarity -
                                    :ARG1 (u5 / unit
                                          :mod c3)
                                    :ARG2 (p8 / province :name (n12 / name :op1 "Ruhr")))))
                  :op4 (m3 / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u6 / unit
                              :mod c)
                        :ARG2 p8)
                  :op5 (h4 / have-03
                        :ARG0 (a11 / and
                              :op1 c
                              :op2 c2)
                        :ARG1 (a12 / and
                              :op1 p8
                              :op2 p3
                              :op3 s4
                              :op4 p4)))))

            :ARG1 c))

It's impossible to breach, I've checked it, and I can keep making those orders for years and years. You stabbed me in Spring 03. It is Fall 05. Instead, I propose that we let you into the Mid Atlantic Ocean and that you help me defend Italy. I can send you past the MAO into West Med, where you can start taking dots like Tunis or Naples. # ::save-date Thu Sep 29, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0020_143.txt

      :op1 (m / move-01
            :ARG1 (u / unit
                  :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France")))
            :ARG2 (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Marseille")))
      :op2 (p2 / possible-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (s / support-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (h / hold-03
                              :ARG1 p))
                  :op2 (s2 / support-01
                        :ARG0 (u2 / unit
                              :location p)
                        :ARG1 (m2 / move-01
                              :ARG1 (f / fleet
                                    :location (s3 / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "Mid-Atlantic" :op2 "Ocean")))
                              :ARG2 (c2 / coast
                                    :location (s4 / south
                                          :part-of (p3 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Spain"))))))))
      :op3 (b / betray-01
            :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 c
            :time (d / date-entity :year 1903
                  :season (s5 / spring)))
      :op4 (p4 / propose-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (a3 / and
                  :op1 (m3 / move-01
                        :ARG1 (f3 / fleet
                              :mod c3)
                        :ARG2 s3)
                  :op2 (s6 / support-01
                        :ARG0 c3
                        :ARG1 (d2 / defend-01
                              :ARG0 c
                              :ARG1 (c4 / country :name (n6 / name :op1 "Italy"))))
                  :op3 (t / transport-01
                        :ARG0 (f2 / fleet
                              :mod c)
                        :ARG1 (f4 / fleet
                              :mod c3)
                        :ARG3 (s7 / sea :name (n7 / name :op1 "Western" :op2 "Mediterranean"))))
            :ARG3 c3))

# ::id dip_train_0023.134 ::date 2022-07-21T10:23:46
# ::snt England will move aggressively on France, pulling France's attention northward while you come in.  A weak Russia and Germany will move on England afterward, reversing the course of England's fleets and staving off his attack on France.  France, who committed defensively to the north, will not be able to ward you off and you can slide in.  England will be next and Russia is falling around this time as well.  Germany will be left and we can figure out a plan from there
# ::save-date Thu Jul 21, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0023_134.txt
(e / expect-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Austria"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (a2 / attack-01
                  :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England"))
                  :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France")))
            :op2 (a3 / attack-01
                  :ARG0 (a4 / and
                        :op1 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                        :op2 (c5 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Germany")))
                  :ARG1 c2)
            :op3 (p / prevent-01
                  :ARG0 (a5 / and
                        :op1 c4
                        :op2 c5)
                  :ARG1 a2)
            :op4 (p2 / possible-01 :polarity -
                  :ARG1 (d / defend-01
                        :ARG0 c3
                        :ARG3 (c6 / country :name (n6 / name :op1 "Italy"))))))

# ::save-date Thu Jul 21, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0023_145.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Austria"))
      :ARG1 (p2 / propose-01
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 (p3 / propose-01
                  :ARG0 c3
                  :ARG1 (a / attack-01
                        :ARG0 (a2 / and
                              :op1 c4
                              :op2 c3
                              :op3 c2)
                        :ARG1 (c5 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "France")))
                  :ARG3 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "England")))
            :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Germany")))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy")))

            :ARG2 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Italy"))
                  :op2 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Germany")))))

      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Austria"))

                  :ARG1 (u / unit
                        :mod (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Russia")))
                  :ARG2 (u2 / unit
                        :mod c3)
                  :ARG3 (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Sweden")))
            :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Germany")))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy")))

# ::save-date Tue Jul 26, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0023_335.txt

                  :season (s3 / spring)))
      :op2 (p2 / propose-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (s2 / support-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (m2 / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                              :mod c)
                        :ARG2 (p3 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Constantinople")))
                  :time (d / date-entity :year 1903
                        :season (f / fall)))
            :ARG3 c2))

# ::save-date Fri Sep 23, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0025_99.txt
(a / agree-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))

            :op1 (h / have-03
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (a3 / and

                        :op2 (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Portugal"))))
            :op2 (h2 / have-03
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (a4 / and
                        :op1 (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Marseille"))
                        :op2 (p4 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Spain"))))

                  :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n7 / name :op1 "Germany"))

                        :op1 (p5 / province :name (n8 / name :op1 "Paris"))
                        :op2 (p6 / province :name (n9 / name :op1 "Belgium")))))
      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England")))

# ::id dip_train_0025.136 ::date 2022-09-23T09:26:24
# ::snt I’m attacking Portugal from Spain- support me from mao and we’ll knock him out
# ::save-date Fri Sep 23, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0025_136.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG1 (s / support-01
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 (a / attack-01
                  :ARG0 (u / unit
                        :mod c
                        :location (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Spain")))
                  :ARG1 (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Portugal")))
            :instrument (f / fleet
                  :location (s2 / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "Mid-Atlantic" :op2 "Ocean"))))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England")))

                  :ARG1 a2)

      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG1 (a / attack-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 (a2 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2)
            :ARG1 (a3 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France")))

                  :ARG1 c)

                  :ARG1 c
                  :ARG2 c2))
      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :polarity (a2 / amr-unknown))

(e / expect-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (h / have-03
            :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia"))
            :ARG1 (p / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Sweden"))
            :condition (a / agree-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (a2 / attack-01 :polarity -
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Berlin")))
                  :ARG2 c)))

# ::save-date Wed Aug 3, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0029_7.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (h / have-03 :polarity -
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
            :ARG1 (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Spain")))
      :op2 (p2 / propose-01
            :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Russia"))
            :ARG1 (h2 / have-03
                  :ARG0 c3
                  :ARG1 (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Norway")))
            :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Germany")))
      :op3 (p4 / possible-01
            :ARG1 (d / defend-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 c2
                  :ARG3 (c4 / country :name (n6 / name :op1 "Turkey")))))

# ::id dip_train_0029.8 ::date 2022-08-03T13:36:01

            :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Russia")))
      :ARG2 (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Berlin"))
      :polarity (a / amr-unknown)
      :time (d / date-entity :year 1901
            :season (f / fall)))

# ::id dip_train_0029.11 ::date 2022-08-03T13:42:20
# ::snt I’m moving from Prussia back to Warsaw. I expanded East too fast and I need to deal with Turkey in the South. I understand if you want to bounce me from Sweden this turn but if you don’t I can more easily deal with my problems in the South and direct my attention away from you to the Balkans.
# ::save-date Wed Aug 3, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0029_11.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (m / move-01
            :ARG1 (u / unit
                  :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Russia"))
                  :location (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Prussia")))
            :ARG2 (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Warsaw")))
      :op2 (p3 / possible-01
            :ARG1 (b / bounce-03
                  :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG2 (u3 / unit
                        :mod (c2 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Germany")))
                  :ARG3 (p4 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Sweden"))
                  :time (d / date-entity :year 1901
                        :season (f / fall)))))

# ::id dip_train_0029.15 ::date 2022-08-03T13:45:49
