(a / and
      :op1 (t / trust-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
            :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia")))

# ::id dip_train_0029.17 ::date 2022-08-03T13:46:50
# ::snt Turkey asked me why your army in Ber halted. What do you want me to say?
# ::save-date Wed Aug 3, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_train_0029_17.txt
(t / tell-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (m / move-01 :polarity -
            :ARG1 (a / army
                  :mod (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                  :location (p / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Berlin")))
            :purpose (a2 / amr-unknown))

                  :ARG1 (a2 / and
                        :op1 c

                  :ARG0 c3

                        :ARG1 (a2 / army
                              :mod c2)
                        :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Warsaw"))))

                  :ARG0 c3
                  :ARG1 (a3 / agree-01
                        :ARG0 c3
                        :ARG1 s
                        :ARG2 c)
                  :ARG2 c)
            :ARG3 c2))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.5 ::date 2022-08-09T09:35:14
# ::snt Would just like to reiterate that Italy would likely take an opportunistic stance towards France - their defensive position is strong enough that I won't attack them proactively, but if they are locked into a conflict with you I might stab them
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_5.txt

# ::id dip_validation_0001.6 ::date 2022-08-09T09:35:27
# ::snt So in that sense Italy is broadly friendly to your interests - if you and France are allied I will leave you alone, but if France is your enemy I could potentially help you to break a stalemate
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_6.txt
(p / possible-01
      :ARG1 (a / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
                  :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany")))))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.7 ::date 2022-08-09T09:35:36
# ::snt But what I'd need in exchange is for you to keep me posted on developments in the west. Are you leaning towards working with England, or France?
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_7.txt
(p / possible-01
      :ARG1 (a / ally-01
            :ARG1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
            :ARG2 (o / or
                  :op1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England"))
                  :op2 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France")))
            :polarity (a2 / amr-unknown)))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.8 ::date 2022-08-09T09:36:30
# ::snt It seems for the moment that both are cooperative, but I'm likely to side with the French from the outset barring difficulties with them. I'll keep you posted, same relationship as previously established. In any case, friendship with the French is not very likely to last past England's demise so I'll definitely need the help then. Thank!
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_8.txt
(e / expect-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (a / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France")))))

# ::snt Unfortunately we only talked very briefly about staying out of each other's ways.

(a / agree-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (a2 / and
            :op1 (a3 / attack-01 :polarity -
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 c2)
            :op2 (a4 / attack-01 :polarity -
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 c))
      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia")))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.15 ::date 2022-08-09T09:48:02
# ::snt Have you talked more with Austria? I must admit to being concerned about you moving to Tyrolia in their defense
# ::save-date Thu Sep 29, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_15.txt
(f / fear-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG1 (m / move-01
            :ARG1 (a / army
                  :mod (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany")))
            :ARG2 (p / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Tyrolia"))
            :purpose (d / defend-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Austria")))))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.16 ::date 2022-08-09T09:49:09
# ::snt Since that would allow the two of you to launch a pretty credible attack on Venetia
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_16.txt
(p / possible-01
      :ARG1 (a / attack-01
            :ARG0 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
                  :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria")))
            :ARG1 (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Venice"))))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.17 ::date 2022-08-09T09:49:40
# ::snt As Germany I generally play somewhat more careful, get them to just promise not to be an enemy until the Western Triple becomes a Western Double. As far as Austria goes, we're allied, hence my preference for Turkey being your foe rather than them. I've no intent of turning South though, not by any means. Don't have the pieces for that.
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_17.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (a2 / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a3 / and
                  :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
                  :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria"))))
      :op2 (e / expect-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u / unit
                        :mod c)
                  :direction (s / south))))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.18 ::date 2022-08-09T10:00:25
# ::snt Yeah, fair enough. I'm planning on a pretty standard opening to Ionian Sea, aiming to convoy to Tunis and with a bounce in Austria
# ::save-date Thu Sep 29, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_18.txt
(e / expect-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (f2 / fleet
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG2 (s / sea :name (n2 / name :op1 "Ionian" :op2 "Sea")))
            :op2 (t / transport-01
                  :ARG0 (f / fleet
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG1 (a2 / army)
                  :ARG3 (p / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Tunisia")))
            :op3 (b / bounce-03
                  :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Austria")))))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.19 ::date 2022-08-09T10:04:01
# ::snt It's a pretty noncommittal move, so will wait and see how things play out
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_19.txt
(a / amr-empty)

# ::id dip_validation_0001.20 ::date 2022-08-09T10:04:08
# ::snt But I'm sure nobody will miss the fact that it sets me up for the Lepanto if the cards fall that wau
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_20.txt
(p / possible-01

            :ARG1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
            :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria"))

      :ARG1 (a2 / and
            :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Russia"))
            :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Turkey"))))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.23 ::date 2022-08-09T10:08:21
# ::snt If they do that, we desperately need to be strongly allied with the Austrians, otherwise they'll roll us over, hard.
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_23.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (a / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 c2
                  :op3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Austria")))
            :ARG3 (a3 / and
                  :op1 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                  :op2 (c5 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Turkey"))))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy")))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.24 ::date 2022-08-09T10:09:20
# ::snt I am also concerned about the Juggernaut, which pushes me towards you and Austria's camp
# ::save-date Tue Aug 9, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_24.txt
(f / fear-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG1 (a / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                  :op2 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Turkey")))))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.26 ::date 2022-08-09T10:15:40
# ::snt Our interests are aligned in both sides of the map, so let's just coordinate closely

      :ARG1 (a2 / and
            :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
            :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany"))))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.27 ::date 2022-08-09T10:16:11
# ::snt I'd be more comfortable committing both fleets east to support Austria against Turkey if I knew you were going to Burgundy (which makes it harder for France to convoy to Tuscany)
# ::save-date Thu Sep 29, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_27.txt
(p / possible-01
      :ARG1 (s / support-01
            :ARG0 (f / fleet :quant 2
                  :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy")))
            :ARG1 (a / attack-01
                  :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria"))
                  :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Turkey")))
            :condition (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (a2 / army
                        :mod (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Germany")))
                  :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Burgundy")))))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.28 ::date 2022-08-10T07:04:46
# ::snt France's F Marseille is a major headache for me
# ::save-date Wed Aug 10, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_28.txt

# ::id dip_validation_0001.29 ::date 2022-08-10T07:07:53
# ::snt What say you?
# ::save-date Wed Aug 10, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_29.txt

# ::id dip_validation_0001.30 ::date 2022-08-10T07:08:00
# ::snt France is definitely going to be a thorn in your side, unfortunately I can neither afford to attack them right now nor likely convince them to not attack you, they're more powerful than I am and I've already pissed off two of my three potentially unfriendly neighbors.
# ::save-date Wed Aug 10, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_30.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (a2 / attack-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
            :ARG1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France")))
      :op2 (p / propose-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (a3 / attack-01 :polarity -
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Italy")))
            :ARG3 c2))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.31 ::date 2022-08-10T07:09:33
# ::snt The Balkan Front is pretty secure for you two though, you can at least hold and with some tricky maneuvering, very easily begin advancing through the Turks.
# ::save-date Wed Aug 10, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_31.txt
(a / amr-empty)

# ::id dip_validation_0001.32 ::date 2022-08-10T07:11:06
# ::snt Understood. Know that Austria and Italy are not going to be able to hold out against Russia and Turkey
# ::save-date Wed Aug 10, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_32.txt
(e / expect-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG1 (d / defend-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 (a / and
                  :op1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria"))
                  :op2 c)
            :ARG3 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                  :op2 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Turkey")))))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.33 ::date 2022-08-10T07:12:14
# ::snt If you want to prevent a juggernaut, we will need whatever help from you we can get
# ::save-date Wed Aug 10, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_33.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG1 (a / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 c
                  :op2 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Austria"))
                  :op3 c2)
            :ARG3 (a3 / and
                  :op1 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                  :op2 (c5 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Turkey"))))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Germany")))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.34 ::date 2022-08-10T07:13:20
# ::snt Well, as I'm sure you've noticed, I've mobilized for the task.
# ::save-date Wed Aug 10, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_34.txt
(a / agree-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy")))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.35 ::date 2022-08-10T07:13:55
# ::snt I've talked to the French to try and get them off your back, but they're dedicated to seeing you off. They told me to tell you that they plan to attack Piedmont with support, which indicates that they're probably planning a convoy to Tuscany. You can't let that happen.
# ::save-date Thu Sep 29, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_35.txt
(w / warn-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (t / tell-01
                  :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France"))
                  :ARG1 (s / support-01
                        :ARG1 (a2 / attack-01
                              :ARG0 c3
                              :ARG1 (p / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Piedmont"))))
                  :ARG2 c)
            :op2 (e / expect-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (t2 / transport-01
                        :ARG0 (f / fleet
                              :mod c3)
                        :ARG1 (a3 / army)
                        :ARG3 (p2 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Tuscany")))))
      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy")))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.36 ::date 2022-08-10T07:27:28
# ::snt Well, it seems the attack on Piedmont with support was genuine, which seems like a very poor decision by the French
# ::save-date Wed Aug 10, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_36.txt
(s / support-01
      :ARG1 (a / attack-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
            :ARG1 (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Piedmont"))))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.37 ::date 2022-08-10T07:27:58
# ::snt Yeah, maybe they predicted that you'd think they were lying to me? Regardless, bad move on their part in any case, especially since you have a build.
# ::save-date Wed Aug 10, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_37.txt
(b / build-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG1 (f / fleet)
      :location (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Rome")))

# ::id dip_validation_0001.38 ::date 2022-08-10T07:40:36
# ::snt Good news for you though. A distracted France is still more than enough firepower to get you through England, and it makes it easy for you to stab them after
# ::save-date Wed Aug 10, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_38.txt
(a / amr-empty)

# ::id dip_validation_0001.39 ::date 2022-08-10T07:41:16
# ::snt I don't know whether you deliberately leaked me that intel thinking I would disbelieve it and go to Tuscany, but no hard feeling if so
# ::save-date Wed Aug 10, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0001_39.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (w / warn-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
            :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy")))
      :op2 (p / possible-01
            :ARG1 (e / expect-01
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 (a2 / and
                        :op1 (t / trust-01 :polarity -
                              :ARG0 c2
                              :ARG2 c)
                        :op2 (m / move-01
                              :ARG1 (u / unit
                                    :mod c2)
                              :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Tuscany")))))))

                  :op1 c

(a / and
      :op1 (b / betray-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Austria"))
            :ARG1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy")))
      :op2 (t / trust-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 c)
      :op3 (a2 / ally-01 :polarity -
            :ARG1 (a3 / and
                  :op1 c2
                  :op2 c)))

            :ARG0 c

                  :ARG1 (a2 / and
                        :op1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                        :op2 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Turkey")))))
      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Italy")))

                  :op1 c

# ::snt The key to not losing to the solo is - assuming the loss of Portugal (which is two coin flips) - not losing 2 of the 3 Russian centers.  You're going to lose STP.  The question then becomes, how to we preserve Warsaw?  My recommendation is:  A: VIE S TYR - BOH A: WAR - UKR A: STP - MOS A: BUD - GAL I: TYR - BOH I: TRI - TYR I: VEN - PIE I: TUS S VEN - PIE T: SEV - UKR T: RUM S WAR - UKR T: ANK - SEV (Convoy)  This plan destroys UKR or ensures that we control it.  It places units in places that they can cut supports on Warsaw which dramatically increases our odds of taking it back if we loose it or maintaining it if we don't.  Chances are, if STP is dislodged, it will be able to retreat to LVN.    Worst case is that Germany just rotates his armies north - supporting himself into LVN and getting three on Warsaw (LVN, PRU, and SIL.  But, we'll either be in Moscow or Galicia (probably both) and Ukraine.  We'll also have two on Munich and he can either keep munich or go after Warsaw.  The other option is to support ourselves into Galicia and Ukraine.  I'm willing to do as you suggest.
# ::save-date Wed Oct 5, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0005_134.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Turkey"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (s / support-01
                  :ARG0 (a2 / army
                        :mod (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Austria"))

                  :ARG1 (a5 / army
                        :mod c3
                        :location (p5 / province :name (n7 / name :op1 "Warsaw")))
                  :ARG2 (p6 / province :name (n8 / name :op1 "Ukraine")))
            :op3 (m3 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (a6 / army
                        :mod c3
                        :location (p7 / province :name (n9 / name :op1 "St." :op2 "Petersburg")))
                  :ARG2 (p8 / province :name (n10 / name :op1 "Moscow")))
            :op4 (m4 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (a7 / army
                        :mod c3
                        :location (p9 / province :name (n11 / name :op1 "Budapest")))
                  :ARG2 (p10 / province :name (n12 / name :op1 "Galicia")))
            :op5 (m5 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u5 / unit
                        :mod c2
                        :location p3)
                  :ARG2 p4)
            :op6 (m6 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u6 / unit

                        :location (p11 / province :name (n13 / name :op1 "Trieste")))
                  :ARG2 p3)

                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 c2)

# ::save-date Thu Sep 29, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0007_260.txt

      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (a2 / attack-01
                  :ARG0 (a3 / and
                        :op1 c
                        :op2 c2)
                  :ARG1 (u / unit
                        :mod (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France")))
                  :instrument (a4 / and
                        :op1 (a5 / army
                              :mod c
                              :location (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Munich")))
                        :op2 (a6 / army
                              :mod c
                              :location (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Warsaw")))))
            :op2 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (a7 / army
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG2 (p4 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Bohemia")))
            :op3 (m2 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (a8 / army
                        :mod c
                        :location (p5 / province :name (n7 / name :op1 "Tyrolia")))))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria")))

From there we can mutually bounce in Budapest while displacing Venice (Assuming that you don't successfully occupy Budapest in Spring). You'll need to hold Budapest on your own power for the first turn though.
# ::save-date Tue Oct 4, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0007_264.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (a5 / army
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Galicia"))
                  :purpose (a2 / attack-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                              :mod (c3 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "France")))))
            :op2 (b / bounce-03
                  :ARG1 (a3 / and
                        :op1 (a6 / army
                              :mod c)
                        :op2 (a7 / army
                              :mod c2))
                  :ARG3 (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Budapest"))
                  :condition (h / have-03 :polarity -
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 p3
                        :time (d / date-entity :year 1907
                              :season (s / spring))))
            :op3 (d2 / dislodge-01
                  :ARG0 (a4 / and
                        :op1 (u6 / unit
                              :mod c)
                        :op2 (u7 / unit
                              :mod c2))
                  :ARG1 (u5 / unit)
                  :ARG2 (p4 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Venice")))
            :op4 (h2 / hold-03
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 p3))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria")))

# ::id dip_validation_0007.265 ::date 2022-08-17T11:20:51
# ::snt Also, if you retreat to the Adriatic you can take Venice uncontested.
# ::save-date Wed Aug 17, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0007_265.txt
(p / possible-01
      :ARG1 (h / have-03
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Austria"))
            :ARG1 (p2 / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Venice")))
      :condition (r / retreat-01
            :ARG1 (f / fleet
                  :mod c)
            :destination (s / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "Adriatic" :op2 "Sea"))))

# ::id dip_validation_0014.21 ::date 2022-09-20T13:10:49
# ::snt well, Russia told me that he was going to bounce me in the black sea.  I figured, what's the worst that could happen?  you bounce him in Rumania?  If i support you in, you only get one build.  So, since you said you were cool with me having greece in the long term, why not go for it in the short term?

      :op1 (t / tell-01

                  :ARG1 (f / fleet
                        :mod c2)
                  :ARG2 (f2 / fleet
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG3 (s / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "Black" :op2 "Sea")))
            :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Turkey")))
      :op2 (b2 / build-01
            :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Austria"))
            :ARG1 (u3 / unit)
            :condition (s2 / support-01
                  :ARG0 c2
                  :ARG1 (m / move-01
                        :ARG1 (u4 / unit
                              :mod c3)
                        :ARG2 (p / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Romania")))))
      :op3 (h / have-03
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 (p2 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Greece"))))

# ::id dip_validation_0014.123 ::date 2022-09-21T10:57:41
# ::snt Italy has gotten himself way out of position. I know you like him, but ... he’s not taking advantage of his opportunity against France and is wide open to attack by us. You could go to Greece and I could go to Rumania and we’d have peace. (I’d have to hold for a turn, so that he doesn’t retreat to Bulgaria).
# ::save-date Wed Sep 21, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0014_123.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 c
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (a2 / attack-01
                  :ARG0 (a3 / and
                        :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Turkey"))
                        :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria")))
                  :ARG1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Italy")))
            :op2 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u / unit
                        :mod c2)
                  :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Greece")))
            :op3 (m2 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG2 (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Romania")))
            :op4 (h / hold-03
                  :ARG0 c
                  :ARG1 p3
                  :purpose (p4 / prevent-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 (r / retreat-01
                              :ARG1 (u3 / unit
                                    :mod c3)
                              :destination (p5 / province :name (n6 / name :op1 "Bulgaria"))))))
      :ARG3 c2)

                  :op1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Turkey"))

# ::snt The key to not losing to the solo is - assuming the loss of Portugal (which is two coin flips) - not losing 2 of the 3 Russian centers.  You're going to lose STP.  The question then becomes, how to we preserve Warsaw?  My recommendation is:  A: VIE S TYR - BOH A: WAR - UKR A: STP - MOS A: BUD - GAL I: TYR - BOH I: TRI - TYR I: VEN - PIE I: TUS S VEN - PIE T: SEV - UKR T: RUM S WAR - UKR T: ANK - SEV (Convoy)  This plan destroys UKR or ensures that we control it.  It places units in places that they can cut supports on Warsaw which dramatically increases our odds of taking it back if we loose it or maintaining it if we don't.  Chances are, if STP is dislodged, it will be able to retreat to LVN.    Worst case is that Germany just rotates his armies north - supporting himself into LVN and getting three on Warsaw (LVN, PRU, and SIL.  But, we'll either be in Moscow or Galicia (probably both) and Ukraine.  We'll also have two on Munich and he can either keep munich or go after Warsaw.  The other option is to support ourselves into Galicia and Ukraine.  I'm willing to do as you suggest.
# ::save-date Wed Oct 5, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0014_271.txt

      :op1 (e / expect-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Turkey"))

                  :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria"))

            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (s / support-01
                        :ARG1 (m / move-01

                              :location (p6 / province :name (n7 / name :op1 "Warsaw"))
                              :mod c2)

                        :ARG1 (a8 / army
                              :location p
                              :mod c2)
                        :ARG2 (p8 / province :name (n9 / name :op1 "Moscow"))))

            :ARG1 (a6 / army
                  :location (p9 / province :name (n10 / name :op1 "Budapest"))
                  :mod c2)
            :ARG2 (p10 / province :name (n11 / name :op1 "Galicia")))

            :ARG1 (a9 / army
                  :mod (c3 / country :name (n12 / name :op1 "Italy"))
                  :location p4)
            :ARG2 p5)
      :op5 (m6 / move-01

                  :mod c3
                  :location (p11 / province :name (n13 / name :op1 "Trieste")))
            :ARG2 p4)

            :ARG0 c3

                  :ARG1 (u8 / unit
                        :mod c3

                        :mod c4)
                  :direction (e / east)))

# ::id dip_validation_0020.1 ::date 2022-09-20T09:16:09
# ::snt Hey England, how are you? I would like to discuss an England/France alliance with you, aimed at taking Germany out quickly. I think if we work together and can trust each other, this could be an amazingly strong alliance. No matter what you decide, I think it would be in both our favor's to leave the English Channel as a DMZ. Let me know if you're interested and we can coordinate moves. Looking forwards to a great game, and good luck!
# ::save-date Tue Sep 20, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0020_1.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
      :ARG1 (a / and
            :op1 (a2 / ally-01
                  :ARG1 (a3 / and
                        :op1 c
                        :op2 c2)
                  :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Germany")))
            :op2 (d / demilitarize-01
                  :ARG1 (a4 / and
                        :op1 c
                        :op2 c2)
                  :ARG2 (s / sea :name (n4 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel"))))
      :ARG3 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England")))

# ::id dip_validation_0020.2 ::date 2022-09-20T09:17:46
# ::snt Hello France, I too am interested in moving east with you and I think a channel DMZ is a great idea.  I'll be doing a fairly standard English opening so let's see how russia and germany open to plan tactics next season.
# ::save-date Tue Sep 20, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0020_2.txt
(a / agree-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
      :ARG1 (a2 / and
            :op1 (a3 / ally-01
                  :ARG1 (a4 / and
                        :op1 c
                        :op2 c2)
                  :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Germany")))
            :op2 (d / demilitarize-01
                  :ARG1 (a5 / and
                        :op1 c
                        :op2 c2)
                  :ARG2 (s / sea :name (n4 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel"))))
      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France")))

      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England")))

# ::id dip_validation_0020.4 ::date 2022-09-20T09:19:51

# ::save-date Mon Oct 3, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0020_4.txt
(m / move-01
      :ARG1 (f / fleet
            :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France")))
      :ARG2 (a / and
            :op1 (s / sea :name (n2 / name :op1 "Mid-Atlantic" :op2 "Ocean"))
            :op2 (p / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Spain"))
            :op3 (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Burgundy"))))

# ::save-date Tue Sep 20, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_validation_0020_7.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (b / betray-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
            :ARG1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France")))
      :op2 (p / propose-01
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 (a2 / ally-01
                  :ARG1 (a3 / and
                        :op1 c2
                        :op2 c3
                        :op3 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Italy"))
                        :op4 (c5 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                        :op5 (c6 / country :name (n6 / name :op1 "Austria")))
                  :ARG3 c)
            :ARG3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "England"))))

                  :mod c))

# ::snt Germany, Austria and Italy are allies against France and Russia.
# ::save-date Thu May 26, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0001_2.txt
(a / ally-01
      :ARG1 (a2 / and
            :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
            :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria"))
            :op3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Italy")))
      :ARG3 (a3 / and
            :op1 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "France"))
            :op2 (c5 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Russia"))))

# ::id dip_0001.3 ::date 2022-05-06T10:39:53
# ::snt We propose an alliance between Germany, Austria and Italy against France and Russia.
# ::save-date Thu May 26, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0001_3.txt
(p / propose-01
      :ARG0 (w / we)
      :ARG1 (a / ally-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
                  :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Austria"))
                  :op3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Italy")))
            :ARG3 (a3 / and
                  :op1 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "France"))
                  :op2 (c5 / country :name (n5 / name :op1 "Russia")))))

# ::id dip_0001.4 ::date 2022-05-06T11:42:18
# ::snt the Italian fleet in Venice
# ::save-date Thu May 26, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0001_4.txt
(f / fleet
      :location (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Venice"))
      :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy")))

# ::id dip_0001.5 ::date 2022-05-06T11:49:14
# ::snt Move the French fleet on the north coast of Spain to the Mid-Atlantic Ocean.
# ::save-date Mon Jun 20, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0001_5.txt
(m / move-01 :mode imperative
      :ARG1 (f / fleet
            :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "France"))
            :location (c2 / coast
                  :location (n3 / north
                        :part-of (p / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Spain")))))
      :ARG2 (s / sea :name (n2 / name :op1 "Mid-Atlantic" :op2 "Ocean")))

# ::id dip_0001.6 ::date 2022-05-06T11:49:26
# ::snt We submit the following orders: (1) Hold the English army in Liverpool in place. (2) Move the English fleet in London to the North Sea. (3) The English fleet in Edinburgh shall support the English fleet in London moving to the North Sea.
# ::save-date Tue Oct 18, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0001_6.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (h / hold-17 :mode imperative
            :ARG1 (a2 / army
                  :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))

      :op2 (m / move-01 :mode imperative
            :ARG1 (f / fleet
                  :mod c
                  :location (p2 / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "London")))
            :ARG2 (s / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "North" :op2 "Sea")))
      :op3 (s2 / support-01 :mode imperative
            :ARG0 (f2 / fleet
                  :mod c
                  :location (p3 / province :name (n5 / name :op1 "Edinburgh")))
            :ARG1 m))

# ::id dip_0001.8 ::date 2022-05-06T11:49:43
# ::snt We propose peace between England, France and Germany.

      :ARG0 (w / we)
      :ARG1 (p2 / peace
            :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
            :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France"))
            :op3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Germany"))))

# ::snt We accept the peace proposal between England, France and Germany.
# ::save-date Thu May 26, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0001_9.txt
(a / agree-01
      :ARG0 (w / we)
      :ARG1 (p / propose-01
            :ARG1 (p2 / peace
                  :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
                  :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France"))
                  :op3 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Germany")))))

# ::id dip_0001.12 ::date 2022-05-06T11:49:59

            :location (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Picardy")))

# ::id dip_0001.13 ::date 2022-05-06T11:50:05
# ::snt Retreat the Italian army from Greece to Albania.

            :location (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Greece")))
      :destination (p2 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Albania")))

# ::id dip_0001.14 ::date 2022-05-06T11:50:09
# ::snt Let the French fleet in the English Channel support the French army in Belgium.
# ::save-date Mon Jun 20, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0001_14.txt
(s / support-01 :mode imperative
      :ARG0 c
      :ARG1 (a / army
            :mod (c / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France"))
            :location (p / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Belgium")))
      :instrument (f2 / fleet
            :mod c
            :location (s3 / sea :name (n / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel"))))

# ::id dip_0001.15 ::date 2022-05-06T11:50:18

                  :op1 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Austria"))
                  :op2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia")))

# ::id dip_0025.5 ::date 2022-05-11T10:07:12

# ::id dip_0025.7 ::date 2022-05-11T10:07:27
# ::snt Oh, gdi.  Now I have to tell a truth that sounds like the most cliched lie in the game: my order update didn't take, I wasn't intending to go to Piedmont.  Yes, I know it sounds ridiculous, but in this case true.
# ::save-date Mon Jun 20, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0025_7.txt
(l / lie-08 :polarity -
      :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG1 (o / order-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 c3
            :ARG2 (m / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u / unit
                        :mod c3)
                  :ARG2 (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Piedmont"))))
      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n / name :op1 "France")))

# ::id dip_0025.8 ::date 2022-05-11T10:07:57
# ::snt Good news is that with your opinion this is more of an opportunity than a disaster (I'd still rather be in Tyrolia where I'm *supposed* to be) - I can bounce you in Mars to help keep you in Burgundy, or if you tell me to eff off, I can move back up to Tyrolia
# ::save-date Tue Aug 2, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0025_8.txt
(p / possible-01
      :ARG1 (o / or
            :op1 (b / bounce-03
                  :ARG1 (u2 / unit
                        :mod (c / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France")))
                  :ARG2 (u3 / unit
                        :mod c3)
                  :ARG3 (p3 / province :name (n3 / name :op1 "Marseille")))
            :op2 (m2 / move-01
                  :ARG1 (u / unit
                        :mod (c3 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Italy")))
                  :ARG2 (p2 / province :name (n / name :op1 "Tyrolia")))))

# ::id dip_0025.9 ::date 2022-05-11T10:08:10
# ::snt Yes, please, go off on adventures elsewhere ...
# ::save-date Mon Jun 20, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0025_9.txt
(m / move-01 :polarity - :mode imperative
      :ARG1 (u / unit
            :mod (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy")))
      :ARG2 (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Marseille")))

# ::id dip_0025.10 ::date 2022-05-11T10:08:17

(a / agree-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Italy"))
      :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France")))

# ::id dip_0029.3 ::date 2022-05-11T10:09:01
# ::snt Wait, so why are you attacking both France and England at the same time?  That seems... dangerous?
# ::save-date Fri May 27, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0029_3.txt
(a / attack-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (a2 / and
            :op1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "France"))
            :op2 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "England")))
      :purpose (a3 / amr-unknown))

# ::id dip_0029.4 ::date 2022-05-11T10:09:06
# ::snt I wasn't attacking them, I had non-aggression with them and I had assumed they would've been preoccupied with Russia at least for a few years. I think I can kick out their army in Holland, and from there I guess we'll see what happens.
# ::save-date Tue Sep 13, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0029_4.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (a2 / attack-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
            :ARG1 (a3 / and
                  :op1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England"))
                  :op2 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France"))))
      :op2 (e / expect-01
            :ARG1 (d / dislodge-01
                  :ARG0 (u / unit
                        :mod c)
                  :ARG1 (a4 / and
                        :op1 (a5 / army
                              :mod c2)
                        :op2 (a6 / army
                              :mod c3))
                  :ARG2 (p / province :name (n4 / name :op1 "Holland")))))

# ::id dip_0029.5 ::date 2022-05-11T10:10:06
# ::snt "non-aggression" doesn't exist in this game, in my experience.  You either have allies who you work with to divide spoils, or you have people fighting you or about to.
# ::save-date Fri May 27, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0029_5.txt
(a / amr-empty)

# ::id dip_0029.6 ::date 2022-05-11T10:10:15
# ::snt Moving Kie-Hel is a clear act of aggression against England.  Which is fine since they attacked you at the same time, but if they hadn't, they certainly would now!
# ::save-date Wed Sep 28, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0029_6.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (t / threaten-01
            :ARG0 c3
            :ARG1 (m / move-01
                  :ARG0 (c3 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Germany"))
                  :ARG1 (f / fleet
                        :location (p / province :name (n2 / name :op1 "Kiel"))
                        :mod c3)
                  :ARG2 (s / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "Heligoland" :op2 "Bight")))
            :ARG2 (c2 / country :name (n / name :op1 "England")))
      :op2 (a2 / attack-01
            :ARG0 c2
            :ARG1 c3))

# ::id dip_0029.7 ::date 2022-05-11T10:10:23
# ::snt I agree, I was mostly relying on the fact that England wouldn't attack France, Russia, AND me at the same time.
# ::save-date Fri May 27, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0029_7.txt
(e / expect-01
      :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "Germany"))
      :ARG1 (a / attack-01 :polarity -
            :ARG0 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 (a2 / and
                  :op1 (c3 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "France"))
                  :op2 (c4 / country :name (n4 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                  :op3 c)))

# ::snt We'll see how things play out

(a / amr-empty)

# ::id dip_0029.9 ::date 2022-05-11T10:10:31
# ::snt England didn't - they *helped* Russia, and given they didn't move to ECH last season, they've clearly been resolving their issues with France.  I would assume they are talking a lot at this point.
# ::save-date Wed Sep 28, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0029_9.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (s / support-01
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 (c2 / country :name (n2 / name :op1 "Russia")))
      :op2 (m / move-01 :polarity -
            :ARG1 (f / fleet
                  :mod c)
            :ARG2 (s2 / sea :name (n3 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel"))
            :time (d / date-entity :year 1902
                  :season (s3 / spring))))

# ::id dip_0029.10 ::date 2022-05-11T10:10:40
# ::snt They're taken ECH now, and even if the support into Sweden proves Russia and England have an alliance there isn't much they can do. I agree that I'm in a bit of a tight spot, but I still have full confidence, especially with you and Austria taking on Russia and Italy so effectively.
# ::save-date Fri May 27, 2022 ::user smosher ::file dip_0029_10.txt
(a / and
      :op1 (h / have-03
            :ARG0 (c / country :name (n / name :op1 "England"))
            :ARG1 (s / sea :name (n2 / name :op1 "English" :op2 "Channel")))
      :op2 (p / possible-01
            :ARG1 (a2 / ally-01
                  :ARG1 (a3 / and
                        :op1 (c2 / country :name (n3 / name :op1 "Russia"))
                        :op2 c))))
